modules.description: Provides functions to create and manipulate monotonic and wall-clock time sources, including getting the current time, calculating durations, and converting between time representations. Works with custom data types for time intervals and timestamps, tailored for low-level system time operations. Used in network protocol implementations and timing-sensitive applications requiring precise time tracking across different operating environments.

Returns the current POSIX time in days and picoseconds, retrieves the local time zone offset in seconds, and provides the clock's picosecond period when available. Operates with integer and 64-bit integer tuples to represent time values. Used for precise time synchronization and timezone-aware timestamp calculations.

Measures time intervals in nanoseconds and retrieves the clock's period when available. It operates with integer values representing time durations and provides precise timing data. Used to track execution duration and verify clock stability in performance-critical applications.
